# Distribution for CommonsBase_Dk (Linux x86)

Ships the `dk0` and `dk1` executables, each built from source as a
per-package opam closure (CommonsBase_Dk.Dk0.Closure / Dk1.Closure) and
republished as a single native executable.

## Dk0 executable

  $ get-object CommonsBase_Dk.Dk0@2.4.2 -s Release.Linux_x86 -m ./bin/dk0.exe -f ${RUNTIME}/Linux_x86-dk0.exe
  \test(pass)
  \dk.object(abi: "Release.Linux_x86", value-id: "oaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa")\;

## Dk1 executable

  $ get-object CommonsBase_Dk.Dk1@2.4.2 -s Release.Linux_x86 -m ./bin/dk1.exe -f ${RUNTIME}/Linux_x86-dk1.exe
  \test(pass)
  \dk.object(abi: "Release.Linux_x86", value-id: "obbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbb")\;
